records.addlTxt:
Defendant Javonte M Cotton in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  
Sara Nicole Volden Schroeder appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Amended Information submitted.  Defense counsel acknowledged receipt of a copy of the Amended Information, waived its reading and entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant.  

Charge amended to: COUNT 1 OBSTRUCTING/RESISTING AN OFFICER, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 946.41(1), 939.51(3)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

COUNT 1:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements made by State, defense, and defendant. 
 
The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 7 MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, Consecutive to any other sentence with credit for 15 days. No good time. 

The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR CONCURRENT with current term of probation.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
 - Serve 60 days in the House of Correction, straight time, no good time- STAYED for use at agent's discretion;
 - Absolute sobriety- no controlled substances or alcohol;
 - AODA assessment; treatment, if needed;
 - Urine screens;
 - Mental health assessment; treatment; if needed;
 - Seek and maintain employment;
 - Participate in job and vocational training;
 - Cognitive thinking intervention counseling;
 - Provide DNA sample if not previously done so- pay surcharge;
 - Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment.  

Appeal rights given.  Filed: Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief and Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
